pageContext.claim: “I mean, I don't even have to ask. I don't have to go around, 'How are we doing with this country or that country?' For the most part, almost every time, we're doing badly. We have deficits with everybody.”
pageContext.analysis: It's not that hard to find countries with which the U.S. runs a trade surplus in goods. At the top of the list are Hong Kong, the Netherlands, the United Arab Emirates, Belgium and Australia.
